+# Codex Writer Findings — PublicMenu Chain: publicmenu-260325-164631-3748
+## Findings
+1. [P1] Missing no-table redirect in `openHelpDrawer` — [`pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:1655`](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L1655) opens the help drawer unconditionally with `setIsHelpModalOpen(true)` and `pushOverlay('help')`, while [`pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:1627`](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L1627) already exposes `currentTableId` and [`pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:1297`](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L1297) exposes `setShowTableConfirmSheet`. That leaves PM-133 unfixed: a no-table user still enters the help drawer instead of being redirected straight to table-code entry. FIX: add `if (!currentTableId) { setShowTableConfirmSheet(true); return; }` at the top of `openHelpDrawer`, then add `currentTableId` and `setShowTableConfirmSheet` to the callback dependencies.
+2. [P2] "Другое" textarea is still hidden only by CSS collapse — [`pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:3767`](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L3767) keeps the form mounted and toggles visibility with `overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300` plus `max-h-0 opacity-0`. That does not satisfy PM-134(a), which requires conditional rendering so the textarea is absent from the DOM until the user taps "Другое". FIX: replace the collapsible wrapper with `{showOtherForm && (...)}` and render the textarea block only when `showOtherForm` is true.
+3. [P2] "Другое" textarea does not autofocus on open — the textarea at [`pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:3769`](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L3769) has no `autoFocus`, so PM-134(b) is still missing and tapping "Другое" will not reliably open the mobile keyboard. FIX: add `autoFocus` to the conditionally rendered `<textarea>` so focus happens on mount.
+4. [P2] Help submit action is still inside the collapsible scroll content — [`pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:3699`](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L3699), [`pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:3713`](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L3713), and [`pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:3776`](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L3776) show the submit button still rendered inside the same expandable block as the textarea. PM-134(c) requires a flex-column drawer with a sticky bottom action area so the button stays reachable when the Android keyboard is open. FIX: make `DrawerContent` a `flex flex-col` container, move the cards/textarea into an `overflow-y-auto flex-1` section, and render the submit button in a bottom bar outside the scroll area only when `showOtherForm` is true, preserving `disabled={isSendingHelp || !helpComment.trim()}`.
+5. [P2] `openHelpDrawer` reopens stale help drawer state — [`pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:1655`](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L1655) does not reset `helpQuickSent`, `sendingCardId`, `showOtherForm`, or `helpComment`, while [`pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:1661`](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L1661) resets them only on close. That leaves PM-135 unfixed: a quick reopen can show the stale success screen or previously open "Другое" state. FIX: reset `setHelpQuickSent(false)`, `setSendingCardId(null)`, `setShowOtherForm(false)`, and `setHelpComment('')` before `setIsHelpModalOpen(true)` in `openHelpDrawer`, then extend the dependency array accordingly.
